Comment: Just finished watching this movie. I enjoyed it! I would recommend viewing it or purchasing it on DVD. Will Smith is a good actor in general. His son Jaden did a good job. His acting wasn't bad and WAS believable.  His fear was believable, the main emotion he needed to present. Not sure why some viewers disliked Jaden's acting so much. There might have been some flaws with the script, but nothing very noticeable unless you're trying very hard to find flaws. Even if I can spot a flaw, glad I'm able to get over it and not let it bug me like some viewers. Also, I don't need an answer for EVERYTHING like some viewers. If Superman picked up a gun and shot somebody with it, I would just say, "interesting" and move on. I wouldn't be like, "Why did he use a gun?" Where did he get that gun from?" "Why that type of gun?" and so on and so on. Every movie isn't for everyone. Some of my favorite movies include, "Life Is Beautiful"-"Sling Blade"-"Saving Private Ryan"-"Driver"-"Blade"-"Big Driver"-"The Exorcist"-"The Man From Nowhere"- "Of Mice and Men"-"Resident Evil"-"Pitch Black"-Razorback"-"The Mule"-"The Warriors"-"Beaches"-"The Good, The Bad, The Ugly"-"What Dreams May Come"-"Jesus of Nazareth"......... just to name a few. Out of 10, 10 being awesome! I give After Earth an 8.  According to Wikipedia, this film grossed $243 million against a net production budget of $128 million.  It was release in 2013 on my birthday for crying out loud.  Thanks so much for putting this movie together!  Will Smith, this is NOT the most painful failure of your career.  Don't feel ashamed about it.  You made a profit, gave you and your son more acting experience, employed many others and many viewers actually enjoyed this film.  So see After Earth people before this planet as we know it comes to an end.

Title: After Earth Official Trailer #1 (2013) - Will Smith Movie HD
Comment: The trailer is a lot better than the movie. I just watched it. The only pro I can think of is that I had a feeling M. Night Shyamalan had a vision of how he wanted his world/universe to be and that can be seen from time to time. But everything else is bad, like really bad. Filled with stupid or completely illogical decisions and events and the idea of the evolved earth is never explained in a way that makes any sense. You can see Will Smith is trying his best do deliver a decent performance and that prevents his performaance from being truly bad (it's just mediocre), but Jaden Smith really didn't knock it out of the park this time. Quite the opposite, that was a really really bad performance. But the worst part by far is the writing. Like seriously 'Denied, sit down!' & 'I like it, but I think it's bad'. The people working on this movie can't possibly have thought that any of these lines were even remotely good. It also doesn't work that it's one of the most predictable and therefore suspenseless (recent) sci-fi movies. It isn't the worst movie ever made or something like that, there were a few good ideas, but it was destroyed in its execution. A 3/10 for me.
